docs.abstract: The F.T.C. chair shot to fame six years ago after publishing an academic article that the company needed to be contained. Legal experts wonder if that time has come.
docs.snippet: The F.T.C. chair shot to fame six years ago after publishing an academic article that the company needed to be contained. Legal experts wonder if that time has come.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 2017, Lina Khan, then a 29-year-old law student, shot to fame with an academic article about why Amazon should be contained. Cutting against prevailing trends in antitrust law, Khan argued that the e-commerce giant was unfairly dominating huge swaths of the American economy.

headline.main: Lina Khan Raises the Heat on Amazon

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni

docs.abstract: Interest in the futuristic, immersive digital world is fading just as Apple plans to debut a virtual reality device.
docs.snippet: Interest in the futuristic, immersive digital world is fading just as Apple plans to debut a virtual reality device.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mark Zuckerberg embraced a digital world known as the metaverse when he said in November 2021 that he was changing his company’s name from Facebook to Meta.

headline.main: Apple Is Stepping Into the Metaverse. Will Anyone Care?
headline.print_headline: Apple Is Stepping Into the Metaverse. Will Anyone Want to Follow?

byline.original: By Kellen Browning and Mike Isaac

docs.abstract: Despite the drawbacks of turning to artificial intelligence in medicine, some physicians find that ChatGPT improves their ability to communicate empathetically with patients.
docs.snippet: Despite the drawbacks of turning to artificial intelligence in medicine, some physicians find that ChatGPT improves their ability to communicate empathetically with patients.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Nov. 30 last year,  OpenAI released the first free version of ChatGPT. Within 72 hours, doctors were using the artificial intelligence-powered chatbot.

headline.main: When Doctors Use a Chatbot to Improve Their Bedside Manner

docs.abstract: In federal court, Satya Nadella and Bobby Kotick opposed an attempt by the F.T.C. to delay Microsoft’s $70 billion acquisition of a video game giant.
docs.snippet: In federal court, Satya Nadella and Bobby Kotick opposed an attempt by the F.T.C. to delay Microsoft’s $70 billion acquisition of a video game giant.
docs.lead_paragraph: Satya Nadella, the chief executive of Microsoft, appeared in federal court on Wednesday to pledge his support for open platforms and consumer choice, underscoring the tech giant’s commitment to closing its $70 billion acquisition of Activision Blizzard over regulators’ objections.

headline.main: Microsoft and Activision Chiefs Testify Merger Will Benefit Consumers
headline.print_headline: Chiefs of Microsoft and Activision Testify That Merger Would Benefit Consumers

docs.abstract: A five-day hearing over Microsoft’s $70 billion acquisition, which the Federal Trade Commission hopes to block, began Thursday in federal court.
docs.snippet: A five-day hearing over Microsoft’s $70 billion acquisition, which the Federal Trade Commission hopes to block, began Thursday in federal court.
docs.lead_paragraph: The first day of a weeklong hearing that could determine the outcome of Microsoft’s $70 billion acquisition of the video game giant Activision Blizzard opened Thursday with a promise from Microsoft: If a federal judge grants an injunction that would delay the deal’s closing, Microsoft could abandon the deal altogether.

headline.main: Microsoft Says It Could Abandon Activision Deal if Judge Delays It
headline.print_headline: Microsoft Could Abandon  Its Deal With Activision

byline.original: By Kellen Browning and David McCabe

docs.abstract: How history has shown that the concentration of A.I. development in the hands of two powerful companies will lead to the technology being deployed in ways that will hurt humanity.
docs.snippet: How history has shown that the concentration of A.I. development in the hands of two powerful companies will lead to the technology being deployed in ways that will hurt humanity.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tech giants Microsoft and Alphabet/Google have seized a large lead in shaping our potentially A.I.-dominated future. This is not good news. History has shown us that when the distribution of information is left in the hands of a few, the result is political and economic oppression. Without intervention, this history will repeat itself.

headline.main: Big Tech Is Bad. Big A.I. Will Be Worse.

byline.original: By Daron Acemoglu and Simon Johnson

docs.abstract: The agency had sued to halt the blockbuster deal last year. Its latest move in federal court would prevent the acquisition from being completed.
docs.snippet: The agency had sued to halt the blockbuster deal last year. Its latest move in federal court would prevent the acquisition from being completed.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Federal Trade Commission sued Microsoft on Monday to stop the company from closing its $69 billion purchase of the video game powerhouse Activision Blizzard, escalating the federal government’s efforts to stymie the largest consumer technology deal in decades.

headline.main: F.T.C. Sues to Stop Microsoft’s Activision Deal From Closing
headline.print_headline: F.T.C. Sues To Stop Deal For Activision

byline.original: By David McCabe and Kellen Browning

docs.abstract: The frenzy over artificial intelligence may be ushering in the long-awaited moment when technology goes wild. Or maybe it’s the hype that is out of control.
docs.snippet: The frenzy over artificial intelligence may be ushering in the long-awaited moment when technology goes wild. Or maybe it’s the hype that is out of control.
docs.lead_paragraph: For decades, Silicon Valley anticipated the moment when a new technology would come along and change everything. It would unite human and machine, probably for the better but possibly for the worse, and split history into before and after.

headline.main: Silicon Valley Confronts the Idea That the ‘Singularity’ Is Here
headline.print_headline: The ‘Singularity’ Is Here. Or Is It? Silicon Valley Nears a Tipping Point.

docs.abstract: The Biden administration is exploring whether it can mount a campaign against Chinese tech giants like Alibaba and Huawei, potentially fueling tensions with Beijing.
docs.snippet: The Biden administration is exploring whether it can mount a campaign against Chinese tech giants like Alibaba and Huawei, potentially fueling tensions with Beijing.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the digital cold war between the United States and China, American officials are increasingly turning their attention to a new target: Chinese cloud computing giants.

headline.main: China’s Cloud Computing Firms Raise Concern for U.S.
headline.print_headline: Cloud Giants From China Worry U.S.

docs.abstract: The latest entry in the franchise has seen strong early demand and a smooth launch, according to the company, which isn’t always the case for Blizzard’s popular titles.
docs.snippet: The latest entry in the franchise has seen strong early demand and a smooth launch, according to the company, which isn’t always the case for Blizzard’s popular titles.
docs.lead_paragraph: Diablo IV, the latest version of a video game franchise that has gained millions of fans over its more than 25 years, has broken internal records for its publisher Blizzard and surpassed more than $666 million in sales since its debut on June 6.

headline.main: Diablo IV Breaks Blizzard Records, Surpassing ‘$666 Million’ in Sales
headline.print_headline: Blizzard Devilishly Marks a Sales Milestone
